  "prompt": "Does Donald Trump believe in global warming?",
  "response": "Donald Trump's stance on global warming, or climate change, has been a topic of significant public interest and debate. During his presidency (2017-2021), Trump expressed skepticism about the scientific consensus on climate change. He has called it a \"hoax\" in the past, though he has also acknowledged that there might be some level of human impact on the climate. His administration rolled back numerous environmental regulations aimed at combating climate change, including withdrawing the United States from the Paris Climate Agreement, which he argued was detrimental to the U.S. economy.\n\nIt is important to note that while Trump has publicly downplayed the urgency of addressing climate change, his administration's policies and statements have generally aligned with a more skeptical or dismissive view of the issue. However, his exact personal beliefs may be nuanced and subject to interpretation based on his statements and actions. For the most current and detailed understanding of his views, it would be best to refer to his recent public statements or interviews.",
